oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Chimney rock
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Rock, known as the "Chimney" on the Pinnacle at Cumberland Gap. It extends upwards from a leafy area. Areas of flat, plowed land with houses can be seen far below.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
